        <h2 id="when-to-reassess">When to Reassess</h2>
        <p>
          Light needs change with the seasons even if you never move the plant. Winter&rsquo;s lower sun angle and shorter days mean the same windowsill spot delivers meaningfully less light than it did in summer &mdash; moving high-light plants closer to a window, or adding a few hours of supplemental grow light, keeps them from stalling out over winter. Check the Grow Light Calculator again each season if a plant that was thriving starts looking stretched or pale.
        </p>
        <p>
          Repotting timing is slower: most houseplants only need sizing up every <strong>1&ndash;2 years</strong>, and a plant that isn&rsquo;t showing any of the repotting signs above doesn&rsquo;t need a new pot on a schedule just because time has passed. Fast growers (pothos, monstera in active growth) may outgrow a pot within a single growing season, while slow growers (snake plant, ZZ plant, succulents) can go several years between repots.
        </p>
